data.current_description: Gets the most recent threat list diffs. These diffs should be applied to a local database of hashes to keep it up-to-date. If the local database is empty or excessively out-of-date, a complete snapshot of the database will be returned. This Method only updates a single ThreatList at a time. To update multiple ThreatList databases, this method needs to be called once for each list.
data.summary_suggestion: Compute threat list differences for database updates
data.description_suggestion: Computes the most recent threat list differences to synchronize a local hash database. Returns incremental diffs that should be applied to maintain an up-to-date threat database. If the local database is empty or significantly out-of-date, returns a complete snapshot instead. Processes one threat list per request; multiple lists require separate calls. Returns threat entry additions, removals, and checksum for validation.
